article.headline: South Alabama 91, West Florida 71
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- With 26 points Carlos Smith led South Alabama to a 91-71 victory over West Florida tonight. The Jaguars (4-1) shot 51.6% from the floor and had a 12-point lead over the Argonauts (1-2) going into halftime. Smith was the leading scorer for South Alabama and also had five assists and made six of his nine 3-point shot attempts. Leandro Buboltz contributed to the Jaguars' win with 21 points, while Demetric Bennett had 15 points and five assists. Daon Merritt chipped in with 10 assists. Barry Durosier led West Florida with 27 points, followed by Marcus Grant with 13 points and Andy Beauchamp with 11. Grant also had eight rebounds.
